===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[موسم]]}} (''mausim'', season) < {{ARchar|[[وسم]]}} (''wásama'', to mark, to brand), through Portuguese and Dutch. <ref>[http://www.bartleby.com/61/21/M0402100.html The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language], Fourth Edition. 2000 Houghton Mifflin</ref><ref>[http://dsal.uchicago.edu/cgi-bin/philologic/getobject.pl?c.7:1:1316.platts A Dictionary of Urdu, classical Hindi, and English] Platts.</ref>

===Noun===
'''monsoon'''

#[[Tropical]] rainy [[season]] when the [[rain]] lasts for several months with few interruptions.

